OL,6,FMr Neal's report did however say the
OL,7,Fchildren told his inspectors "they
OL,8,Ffelt safe and happy in the hotels",
OL,9,Fbut that "considering the journeys and
OL,10,Flife experiences" they have had, he
OL,11,Fwas "not surprised".
OL,13,FHe also addressed the issue of
OL,14,Fchildren going missing from hotels -
OL,15,Fand that there are 147 children who
OL,16,Fremain unaccounted for.
OL,18,FAll hotels housing unaccompanied
OL,19,Fasylum seeking children have now been
OL,20,Fclosed.
