OL,6,FDame Diana Johnson, the chair of the
OL,7,FHome Affairs Committee, raised
OL,8,Fconcerns about the the fact David Neal
OL,9,Fhasn't been replaced in his role -
OL,10,F"The Home Office will really need to
OL,11,Fup its game if it is to ensure the
OL,12,FIndependent Chief Inspector of Borders
OL,13,Fand Immigration is restored to where
OL,14,Fit should be, if it is to be a crucial
OL,15,Fpart of testing and developing the
OL,16,FUK's borders and immigration
OL,17,Fstrategies."
OL,19,FMr Neal telling MPs he was fired for
OL,20,F"doing his job".
