OL,6,FIn written evidence sent to the
OL,7,Fcommittee, Mr Neal called for the
OL,8,Fwatchdog role to have greater powers
OL,9,Fand more resources in order to fully
OL,10,Fscrutinise and hold its decisions to
OL,11,Faccount.
OL,13,FMr Neal also denied a suggestion by
OL,14,FHome Secretary James Cleverly that he
OL,15,Fhad been afforded the opportunity to
OL,16,Freapply for his role, telling MPs that
OL,17,Fwas "not the case".
